description_html:
Requirements

  • Sr Bigdata Engineer with atleast 4+ years of experience in big data platform.
  • Must have hands-on experience with cloudera Hadoop and its tools like - Hive, Impala and Spark (all three tools must). HDFS, YARN.
  • Expert in writing Complex SQL Queries.
  • Able to write Linux Shell Scripts.
  • Experience building or maintaining ETL processes
  • Experience with Python, SQL, and data visualization/exploration tools
  • Familiarity with the AWS ecosystem specifically RedShift and RDS
  • Communication skills, especially explaining technical concepts to non-technical business leaders
  • Comfort working in a dynamic, research-oriented team with concurrent projects

description_html:
1.1 Critical Requirements

(a) Web Application Client-side Technologies JavaScript ESS/6, ReactjS, HTMLS/CSS, AJAX/JSON)

(b) Web Application Server-side Technologies (Asp.NET MVC, C#, Python)

(c) Web GIS Technologies (ArcGIS JavaScript APIv4.5, ArcGIS Server REST API, Leaflet, Mapbox, CartoDB, Geoserver, Google Map)

1.2 Other Requirements

It will be advantageous for the candidate to have good worki ng knowledge in the following areas:

a. Development experience using JavaScript technologies (ReactJS, Redux, BabelJS, Webpack, jQuery, D3)

b. Web/mobile User Interface des ign experience

c. ESRI Technologies (ARCG IS Server, ARCMap, geo-processing tools using ARCpy)

d. Open-source technologies such as NodeJS, GeoServer, PostGIS and PostgreSQL.

e. JavaScript testing technologies (Enzyme, chai, mockery, etc.)

f. Containerization technologies and deployment (Docker, Kubernetes) g. Code version control system (Git)

h. DevOps workflow and application
